      "transcript": "you know there's one person who's cutting down the wood there's one person who's getting the graphite that goes inside the pencil someone else in another part of the world is getting hold of the rubber that goes into the eraser but actually there is no single person who is the architect of that entire process and I remember reading that and thinking god that's fascinating because now I understand how a pencil is made and I wish I could understand the same thing about all of the objects that surround us you know if you're watching this on a smartphone this device is something that you know potentially millions of people will have had a hand in and they they will have come from all over the world when you look at device often it's You know, it says, it might say made in Korea, it might say made in China, but actually it's probably made in hundreds of different places, many different factories around the world. Out of all of these different minerals, which we don't spend all that much time thinking about, yeah, our outlook as consumers is often quite narrow.",
